main event: A civilian observed an unidentified object in the sky near Vineland, New Jersey on June 11, 1966.
interesting points: The object was described as oval-shaped and moving quickly, appearing the size of a pea before disappearing., The observation lasted for about 1 minute., The military concluded that it was likely a satellite (Echo II)., The witness reported the object did not have any running lights and made no sound., The witness also had a prior sighting of a similar object on August 24, 1966.
witness description: a 16-year-old male interested in astronomy and UFOs
